14/01/2003
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Nearly 60 per cent of elementary school teachers took part in a national strike Monday (13 January) and promised to continue protests Tuesday. The Croatian Teachers' Union estimates some 25,000 people participated, demanding wage hikes that would put salaries on par with those in other public sectors.
In other news, a team of doctors from the UN war crimes tribunal is expected to examine retired Gen Janko Bobetko in Zagreb on Tuesday. Croatia insists the 83-year-old is too ill to travel to The Hague to stand trial. (Vjesnik - 14/01/03; HINA, HRT, Infopress, HINA, HRT - 13/01/03)
